cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.CE, cs.SY, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the concept of network slicing in 5G mobile networks and the admission control system for processing slice requests, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper mentions the emerging type of public cloud environment, Slice-as-a-Service (SlaaS), which involves distributed computing and resource allocation.
3. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper uses mathematical models to study the rational strategies of impatient tenants waiting in queue-based slice admission control system, which falls under the scope of computational engineering.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the admission control system for processing slice requests based on service level agreements (SLAs) and current (and predicted) resource availability, which involves control systems.
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not the main focus of the paper, the concept of sharing information between infrastructure providers and tenants may have security implications, which falls under the scope of cryptography and security.
